Descriptive Statistics of UXprobe dataset.

Mohamedhakim Elakhrass

March 15, 2016

Below you will see a summary of the dataset from UXprobe. The dataset contains six variables. Session, task, event, eventType, user, and startTime.

session <- count(data, 'session')
task <- count(data, 'task')
event <- count(data, 'event')
eventType <- count(data, 'eventType')
user <- count(data, 'user')

summary(session[,2])
##     Min.  1st Qu.   Median     Mean  3rd Qu.     Max. 
##    1.000    1.000    1.000    2.033    1.000 5914.000
summary(task[,2])
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##       1      13     451   36690   19620  461000
summary(event[-1,2])
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##     1.0     4.0    37.0  2060.0   314.5 56540.0
summary(eventType[,2])
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##       1   12560  137500  212800  184400  729700
summary(user[-1,2])
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##     1.0     6.0    31.0   159.2   144.0  4239.0
